{
  "doc_id": "30016",
  "text": "An operon, consisting of eight genes (fdhAB-mhyCDE-FGH), was isolated and sequenced from T. litoralis. The operon codes for a formate dehydrogenase and a [NiFe] hydrogenase which belongs to the group of H 2 -evolving, energy-conserving membrane-associated hydrogenases. Remarkably, the operon could be found only in P. abyssi among the four closely related species (P. furious [CITATION_1] , P. abyssi [CITATION_2] , Pyrococcus horikoshii [CITATION_3] , Thermococcus kodakaraensis [CITATION_4] ) whose genomes were sequenced, although the other soluble and membrane-associated hydrogenases are widespread among the members of the Thermococcaceae family.",
